The paper proposes a novel approach for the formal verification of biological systems using a modal linear logic. This involves the use of formal logic and automated theorem proving, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a Lambda Prolog prover for partial automation of the proofs, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with the dynamic behavior of biological systems, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of a Coq Proof Assistant for formalizing the proofs suggests that the paper could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the formal verification of biological models, which suggests that it could belong to the Mathematical Software (cs.MS) sub-category.
